The paper deals with Distributed Denial-of-Service (DDoS) attacks, which fall under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for identifying botnets, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes an inference algorithm, which falls under the category of statistical inference (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
